      "content": "Now I have a clear picture of the existing test structure. The new tests need to cover three things:\n\n1. The core fix: `(if (pred? x) #t #f)` inside a lambda (tail position, branches wrapped in `MenaiIRReturn`) now optimises to just the predicate result\n2. The type-safety guard: `(if non-boolean-expr #t #f)` must still raise a type error\n3. The `match` pattern that was the original motivating case",
