    {
      "id": "2be87bb8-62ee-484e-8194-e9dda22f0ada",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-08T11:33:40.718450+00:00",
      "type": "ai_response",
      "content": "Here's what was added and why each test exists:\n\n---\n\n### `TestReturnWrappedBranches` (3 unit tests)\n\nThese test the optimizer directly with hand-constructed IR, specifically the structure the IR builder actually emits for tail-position branches \u2014 `MenaiIRReturn`-wrapped constants inside the `MenaiIRIf`, rather than bare constants outside it. This is what the old code was blind to:\n\n- **`test_identity_fires_with_wrapped_branches`** \u2014 `(if (pred? v) Return(#t) Return(#f))` \u2192 `Return(pred? v)`. Verifies the core fix: the optimizer now sees through the wrapper.\n- **`test_negation_fires_with_wrapped_branches`** \u2014 same for the `#f/#t` \u2192 `boolean-not` path.\n- **`test_non_boolean_condition_not_rewritten_with_wrapped_branches`** \u2014 a non-predicate builtin (e.g. `integer+`) as the condition must not be rewritten even with wrapped boolean branches, because doing so would bypass the VM's runtime type check.\n\n### `TestBooleanIdentityIntegration` additions (4 integration tests)\n\nThese exercise the full pipeline end-to-end:\n\n- **`test_match_predicate_pattern_optimised`** \u2014 the original motivating case: `(match c ((? string? s) #t) (_ #f))` inside a lambda. Verifies correct results across string and non-string inputs.\n- **`test_match_predicate_negation_pattern_optimised`** \u2014 same with inverted arms (`#f`/`#t`), exercising the `boolean-not` path via `match`.\n- **`test_non_boolean_condition_preserves_type_error`** \u2014 `(if \"hello\" #t #f)` and `(if 42 #t #f)` must still raise at runtime. This is the soundness regression test for `_is_boolean_typed`.\n- **`test_non_boolean_condition_in_and_preserves_type_error`** \u2014 `(and \"hello\" #t)` and `(or 1 #f)` must still raise. These are the exact expressions that broke before `_is_boolean_typed` was added, because `and`/`or` desugar to `(if x y #f)` which has the `#t`/`#f` pattern but with a non-boolean condition.",
      "completed": true,
      "usage": {
        "prompt_tokens": 141338,
        "completion_tokens": 585,
        "total_tokens": 141923
      },
      "model": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
